content.detailedDescription: We were coming back from dinner at a restaurant from a nearby town. (dixon, il.) at about 9 pm.  i was with my fiance and future mother and father in-law. my future in-laws just took us out for our engagement dinner celebrating out marriage coming up in september.  about 5 or 6 miles from sterling i saw a very bright light low to the south maybe 10 degrees above the horizon, and stationary.  this interested me being an amateur astronomer (have a questar 7) for about seven years, and being familiar with venus, jupiter and other bright objects in the night sky.  the sun had set about an half hour earlier and just a faint glow of twilight was in the west, but basically it was dark. chicago being 100 miles to the east, it is not uncommon to see large commercial planes coming at you directly from the east with their landing lights still on slowly gaining altitude without any apparent motion, but as the craft comes closer motion can be finally detected and increases as they eventually pass overhead or therabouts.  but this was different.  it was motionless, and motionless.  i kept quiet, being that i was the only one having seen it so far, and waited for it to move marking it in sky visually.  it did not. i remarked then almost a minute later about this unusual motionless bright object. as we got closer it was apparent we were on a course to intercept this object. by this time i was quite excited and captivated as we approached the main highway where this object was hovering. with the object just 100 yards or less my father in- law (pulled onto the highway trying to watch and drive at the same time. i told him to puill over aobut 3 times and finally he pulled off onto the shoulder behind several other cars with people already out of their cars and watching this object.  it was captivating. i have tried to find the drawings i made afterwards and notes i have yet to find them.  back then i told this story many times in detail to a point it became ingrained in me but now 32 years later the estimation in size may be slightly off but i believe well within the ballpark. but here goes. when we got out of the car the object was coming right at us slowly maybe 10-15 miles an hour. i  when it became alarmingly close (70 yards?) and maybe 45 degrees up, i then got a good look at the size and shape of this thing.  i had been an airman in the navy for 4 years, (66-70) working with the a-6a intruder as a plane captain receiving many of these and other jet aircraft types as well on the flightline and on carrier parking them for post flight inspections, but i have have never received one of these babies and didn't really want to chalk this guy.  it was approx. 65-75' in diameter, disk shaped, and about 10,and brilliantly lit up. before it broke out of its pattern, it made about 6or 7 rectanglar passes each time coming at us raising up to its' closest point and then banking slightly (tilted) to the direction (west) for about 75 yards, south for 100 yards, 75 yards to the east then at us (100 yards) to the north doing this 6-7 times.  being dark without the lights was impossible to tell the shape except for the lights. the lights! spectacular almost hypnotic at times.  the ten foot heighth of the craft was divided up into about 5'wide by 10 high panels side by side each fully lit. (from inside?) outlining the shape as disk  shape.  but each panel went on and off and synchronized, moving rotating completely around the craft all the time it made these passes.  the motion was quite rapid as i recall and at times had a reverse movement. it reminded me when as a boy i would turn my bicycle upside down, crank the pedal as fast as i could get it and watch the wheel and spokes make that reverse motion similar to some affects i've seen in the aurora borealis. almost hynotic and quite spectacular. anorher unsusal thing i noticed was that it made no sound.  the only sound i heard an almost undetectable sound of the wind being cut as it rotated. a gentle cutting of the wind. in my mind i am gong over all the possible things this could be and i was coming up with a zero.  plane? moving too slow and no noise. helicopter? no noise, too small. balloon or dirigible? don't think so. so what was it. i mentioned to linda i wanted to run across the highway before its next pass, lie down in the grass and wait for it to pass overhead to get even a closer look, but she would not let me. and to tell you the truth part of me wanted to go and part of me said stay put which i did. finally it slowly broke pattern and went off to the east. we were all getting into our vehicles when the person ahead said it was a helicopter but it could not have been. as we were coming into town still in sight i noticed it had now turned on colored maybe even blinking lights and then i lost sight of it. the next day i looked for headlines concerning this sighting especially being seen by scores, but i saw nothing in the newspapers. it was said that it was a dirigible hired to make passes over a nearby residence in celebration of someones birthday and i always had a problem with that explanation being there was not a house close. thank you for listening.  it is unusual with such a spectacular, captivating and entertaining tool at our use it has never been seen again to my knowledge any where else. jim stroup
content.summary: At night, large, disk shaped, spectacular color, no noise, close prox., slow rectangular passes, 60' off ground, 20 minutes.

content.detailedDescription:
I was up early to take an early swim which i rarely do. i needed to be back early to meet some contracted men who were to remodel our basement flooring. it was dark when i left for the pool. it was dawn when i drove home. the moon was huge and striking-looking at the horizon. i drove down our road. my mind was on getting breakfast. i saw a metalic gray form above the road and took it for another airplane getting ready to land at the nearby airport. then i noticed it wasn't moving. i looked carefully at it to make sure it wasn't moving. it wasn't. it was cigar shaped, no protrusions top or bottom, rounded ends,no windows, etc. it had an appealing gray metalic shiny surface. glossy like the wet gray pebbles in a tanguy painting. this glossy surface appealed to me as in a tanguy painting. i was thinking of going to the house, seconds from where i had stopped, for binoculars. but when i got to our driveway i saw the men had already arrived and i had to deal with them.


later that day at around 7pm est at night i saw a huge pink/mauve flower-like brightening just above the trees. i took it for some strange star. i called to my wife who confirmed it. when i returned it was gone. i could see it was a very clear night with lots of bright stars. the object had shut out the other stars with its brightness. asid from northern lights, which are shaped differently, i have never seen such color in such an object in the sky, including the sun at sunrise or sunset. the rays of light coming from its center were dense and looked like petals of flowers with dense, slender shapes. not unlike a seas anemone.
content.summary: Saw metalic gray cigar-shaped object hovering low in sky.

content.detailedDescription: I am reporting this on behalf of my co-workers. they know i often see these types of thing and are embarrassed but astounded by what they saw. two witnesses traveling in separate vehicles on the same stretch of road at approx. 5:30am march 13th met at work and excitedly asked each other if they "saw that thing over the golf course". i arrived a few minutes later at the office and they described it to me. description: elongated, orange/amber glowing edge of a possible craft of unknown size and shape. they both could make out that there was something large and dark trailing behind the glowing light and that the light was "attached" to the object. the glowing portion was symmetrical. when one of the witnesses stopped and got out of the vehicle to observe, she noticed a "twinkling" or "ember-type" of material lightly "sprinkling" or "trickling" down from the lighted area. the craft moved very slowly from north to south and was within the city limits. the distance above the ground was approx. 600-800ft. or "two or three football fields up". both witnesses were pressed to get to work so the longest encounter lasted about 2 minutes. 10 minutes after the event was first witnessed i drove around the area to see if i could spot it. i didn't see anything. i spoke to a person on the golf course that was outside working during the event, he did not get a look at it either.
content.summary: Elongated, amber glow - slowly moving across the horizon, 600-800 ft. above ground.

content.detailedDescription:
I am writing to help corroborate the lady form illinois' testimony.

no, she's not crazy!

i saw nearly the same thing in april of 2007 at approximately 0330am flying over my home in northeastern kentucky.

i was having a bout with insomnia, and decided to go outside and videotape and observe some of the strange goings on in the airspace above my home.

i saw a light flying through the air, coming from the north and headed due south and it was making no noise.  i decided to start taping it when to my joy, i noticed another light approximately 200 feet away, on the firsts starboard wing, and i distinctly remember saying, "hmmm, that's strange, the one on the left is flying awfully close to the one on the right, but it's cool, because there are two of them!"

within about 10 seconds of making the above statement, my knees almost buckeled, and a great deal of fear came over me, because it dawned on me that, no, i wasn't looking at two different lights on two different aircraft, but i was looking at one huge aircraft!!!  and it was flying extremely low!

i mean, it looked like it was just barely clearing a large grove of huge probably two century old oak trees, which are at least 50 feet tall.

it was then that i noticed, out of the corner of my right eye, that there was another light, to the right (port side) about 200 feet away...So this thing was h-u-g-e!

i remember saying outloud, "oh my god!  this is one huge f-ing thing, and it's so damn low, that yes, i am scared [cms/tg/pd] right now!!!"

it was then that i truly realized the enormity of the thing.  it was at least 300-400 wide and maybe that much long, if not more!

it had three white lights on each "corner", and one red light dead center underneath, whith six pale white/yellow lights in rows of two center around the red light underneath.  it also had deep blue looking lights on the underside of each corner.

it was so huge.  it flew directly over top of me, my house and my yard, headed due south.  

i had my video camera running the whole time, and i know that my voice probably sounded at least an octave higher in pitch, and that i was talking twice as fast as normal.

i was able to clearly see all of these details, as there was a full moon, and it was in the low in the sky in the south/southwest, with a few clouds, but mostly clear.

when this thing flew over me, i believe i was more scared because it was so low, rather than the fact that it was huge!

i was so big, that when it flew over, it literally blocked out the star field for about 10-20 seconds, which i know that i stated while i taped it flying over me.  

it appeared to be completely stable in flight, was quiet, but had a very low pitched rumble to it...You could feel it more than you could hear it.  it was really creepy sounding.  it sounded like a sub woofer which had a really low frequency noise on it, turned up and placed on a carpeted floor.  weird.

it flew really slow.  extremely slow...Like a blimp in flight.  come to think of it, it might have sounded like a blimp's engine, except lots more quiet.

also, and this is really strange...As i watched it fly over, i noticed that a willow tree which was in my front yard, and which had not yet bloomed, or had leaves, started shaking.  i mean, the really longs and slender branches, were almost quivering.  i tried to videotape them, but i'm sure you could not see them in the darkness, but they were shaking. what drew my attention to this anomaly was that i heard them first.  i then noted that there was absolutely no wind, so i was further creeped out!

i then watched it fly on a continuous southerly heading, and approximately 1/2 mile away, it made a slow bank to starboard, and floated toward the south/southwest, which gave me a really good look at it.  

it was not black, but almost an air superiority gray color, and it was definetely triangular shaped.

after i saw this, i came into the house, and was shaking.  i even woke my wife up, and she immediately sensed something had shaken me up.

lastly, although i did videotape this...Thing, i have never, gone back and reviewed the tape, because it creeped me out so bad!  i still have it, but i have not worked up the gumption to re-live that period in time!
content.summary: Huge triangle over kentucky...To corroborate what lady from ilinois said.

content.detailedDescription:
To give you some background, i am a trained observer, and am a military officer and i know what different aircraft look like and sound like, and what they are capable (and not capable) of doing while in flight.

i had been noticing triangular shaped light patterns of various sizes flying through the airspace above my home in the sharkey area of rowan county since january of 2007.  

i had been awakened one saturday am, around 0530 by the sound of extremely low flying single engined jet aircraft (f-16's).  when i jumped out of bed to look out the window to see what the hell was going on, i looked out a bedroom window facing east and saw 5 lights, stacked one on top of the other, and just appearing to hover in the same area.  when the two f-16's got to the vicinity of the 5 lights, the same 5 lights, literally shot off in 5 different directions, and were gone.  

it was at that moment that i started to "pay attention" to what was overhead. 

i started waking up really early in the morning, and started videotaping some extremely strange looking, strange acting aircraft. 

i started seeing trends and patterns of flight at different times throughout the day (i have an office in my home).  i started seeing (and taping) various sized triangular shaped aircraft at night...Some completely silent and some completely noisy.  some small, some large.  

i also started seeing some weird strobing lights, that appeared to come out of nowhere.  not your normal commercial of general aviation aircraft type strobes, but, ones that flashed so fast, that the aircraft appeared to "jump" across the sky.  

i also noticed that every monday-thursday am, at exactly 0345, there would be a plethora of aircraft flying from every cardinal direction, crossing the airspace above my home.  several appear to be triangular shaped and vary from large to small, fast and slow, completely noisy, to completely quiet/no sound at all!  

now, here's the deal...I live one mile from a new general aviation airport, which was not yet finished when i started noting all of this, but i live at a minimum, one hour from the nearest commercial airports and most only have flights leaving at 0530. 

i know for a fact that some of these aircraft are b-2's, as i have seen them do flyovers, and i know what their engine "note" sounds like.  i also know what their contrails (when they leave one....Which isn't often) look like.  i also know what their light pattern looks like when i see them.

however, i have also seen small and medium sized triangular shaped craft, which make absolutely no noise, and leave no contrail, which have done some pretty amazing aeronautical feats.  i saw one, literally (and i have this on tape) spin around 2 times, while maintaining an e to w heading.  it did not slow down, speed up, bank, or fall out of the sky.  i also saw one (on tape also), go from a w heading, to a a sse heading instantly!  it made nearly a 240 turn, without slowing down!  and, with no noise.  none!  

i've also seen lights(on tape as well), which had two stacked on top of one another, and watched them change elevation and appear to change places with each other, without any noise. 

one morning, at around 0600, my wife yells up to our bedroom, from downstairs, "honey, you have got, to come down here and see this!"  so, i jumped out of bed, ran downstairs and looked through the blinds of a window which faces due south.  low and behold, right there, over one of the ponds in our subdivision, is a black, triangular shaped aircraft, making absolutely no noise, literally hovering over this pond, no more than 1000 feet off the deck!!!  i am not one to get easily excited over things, especially during a crisis, but i almost soiled myself!  i was flabbergasted at what we were seeing!  my heart rate jumped up, and i literally rubbed my eyes, because i thought i was dreaming.  i recall saying to my wife, "am i really seeing a black triangular shaped aircraft hovering and making no noise?  i'm am awake, right?!"

i told my wife to run upstairs and get me some pants and a shirt, because i am going to videotape this, because no one will believe this, and as soon as i go out side in my skivvies, one of the neighbors will be out walking there dog!  while she did this, this...Craft, did some other amazing things.  #1  it waggled its wings, #2 it then flew backwards a short distance, #3 it then stopped, hovered, then, #4 waggled its wings again, pitched the nose slightly down, then #5  went forward again, then stopped, hovered, and unfortunately, before i could get outside to videotape, it shot off like a bat out of hell, and was gone!!!  no noise, nothing!  my wife asked it were a harrier or something.  i said, "no f-ing way!  if it were a harrier, there wouldn't be a window left in the neighborhood, because they are uber loud!" 

we are baffled to this day, as to what the hell it was, why it was hovering over our subdivision and how it didn't make any sound.  and, i could kick myself for not being able to videotape it.  i found out later, that it is possible to videotape through the window by putting the camera through the blinds and using them as a sort of makeshift tripod.

i think, it is a secret military black project aircraft, and i sincerely hope...It's one of ours, because as will smith's charecter said in independence day, "i got to get me one of these!"
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Strange aircraft over kentucky...

content.detailedDescription:
I have been looking to the the western sky the past few days due to hearing of a strange light in the night sky that reportedly appears just after sunset. 
i looked to the west and spotted a stationary orange planet like light. this was the brightest  light in the sky. the sky was cloudless. i could see the stars clearly. 
the light faded in and out, from dim and small to bright and bigger. 
i called my husband to come and take a look. he saw the light too. then he pulls out a green laser that is very powerful and he points it at the light in the sky. then my husband blinks the laser twice. the light suddenly blinks out. we have not seen the light again this evening.
we will looking out for and will report back any happenings.
content.summary: Star-like object in sky, stationary orange tinge.

content.detailedDescription: The first picture is a non blown up ufo and the second is what it looks like when you blow it up, and you can see alien heads looking you.  the third picture is of another ufo blown up and looks like a demon.  these pictures were taken on the fourth day.

content.detailedDescription:
This happened in the late 80's at summit lake in the monongalia national park. it was right around dusk. the sun was settings and the sky was very clear. some friends and i went to the lake to hang out for awhile. we were not drinking or doing any type of drugs. there was five of us all together. 
  we had parked in the boat ramp area. as we were standing around talking not long after we arrived, my one friend danny, said he noticed a light which appeared to be comming up through the tree line on a distant hill. at first noone else saw this. after a few minutes it became visable that something was there. at the spot we were standing it was hard to say if it was comming closer or was rising  from behind the hillside when we all first saw it together. as it got closer we all noticed it was not making any noise at all. if i had to guess the height in which it flew over us, i would have to say 300-400 feet above us. as it got closer it was obvious it was triangle shaped with a white light on each corner. it practically went directly over us and kept going over the horizon towards the town of richwood. which was the closest town to where we were. we did not see anything else after it had gone over the horizon. it wasnt moving at a high rate of speed. it was slow enough to make out the shape and the lights.
  i have not seen any of my friends from that night in almost 20 years. oddly enough, danny and i got in touch a few weeks ago on the phone. he brought this up to me after all this time. he thought he would ask me if i remembered this event and i did. he said he wanted to make sure he wasnt imagining it after all these years. 
  all our lives we had heard there was a secret military base hidden in the mountains. i have never seen or heard anything to this day that would prove the rumor. but that night made me wonder if they were true. i have never seen anything like that ever again.
content.summary: Object appeared in the distance and flew overtop of us.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking my dog in the morning when i noticed a bright white light off in the distance. i didn't pay to much attention to it, thinking it was just an airplane. after a minute the light was closer and i could notice two blinking white lights behind it. again, i assumed it was an airplane's winglights. after a few more minutes heard a low humming noise and looked above me. floating by was a low flying large trianglular craft. the tip of it emitted a bright white light and the two end point had blinking blue lights. the bottom of the craft had 3 rows of thin dim yellow lights. after i had noticed it, it changed direction by about 70 degrees bearing north and then headed almost due west towards chicago. the light remained in sight for several minutes after the event, then i lost it beyond a treeline. during and after the event i was terrified. this may have been the most terrifying expirience of my life. i have contacted local authorities and local airports, none of which report unusual activity or craft in the area at the time. no reports on this have been filed either.
content.summary: Black triangle seen flying overhead.

content.detailedDescription: I work for a preschool and every morning a co-worker and i do a bus route.  about a month or so ago we seen a light in the sky during our morning bus route, the light would stay on for about 10 secs and then turn off for about 10 secs.  on march 11, in the same location on our bus route we seen a very bring light in the sky.  the time was around 6:45 am.  as we moved towards the lights (driving east) they were also moving towards us (flying west).  they lights banked and turned north - northwest.  as they turned we seen it was three lights that made a delta or triangle shape.  there was no blinking lights with the first sighting or this sighting.  in this area, we are close to the fort smith airport and could have easliy been an airplane.  but the shape and lack on any blinking light is why i am reporting this.
content.summary: Delta shape lights.

content.detailedDescription:
At 5:45 this a.M. (3/12/09) i walked out on my deck which overlooks the hoodcanal. i saw a bright star like object about 20 degress up from the north western horizon. as i watched it, it pulsated about every 5-10 seconds with a bright green, back to yellowish white star shape, another 5-10 seconds with a bright red pulse, back to yellowish white star shape, 5-10 seconds with a bright white pulse, then back to its original color. thinking possible plane (as many plans fly over that area) i continued to watch it. it did not behave like a plane. i expected it to diminish in size if it was flying away from me, or get larger if it was flying towards me. it did neither, instead it moved slowly from left to right. i estimated the object to be 5-10 miles from my location. from my porch it travled the length of a yard stick in one hour. if estrapulated to say 10 miles i don't know how far that is. however, it was moving very slowly towards the right. about every 15 minutes it would do a quick strobe like effect with red, green and white.. it performed quite a light show. i found it very unusual as the pulses were very bright. at that distance of course there was no noise, however i did see two planes fly fast toward the opject i could not tell what kind of planes flew towards it but they were the ones i see at night occassionaly with the extreemly bright strobe lights which go off and you don't see anything for about ten seconds and then a very strong white strobe lights again. they appeared to circle the object i was watching as they appeared in a circle about 5 in from the object from where i was. when the sun came up at about 7:10 this a.M. i saw a very thick fog bank from the horizon up to the same hight as the 
object. i estimated the fog bank about 20 miles from my porch, which means the object was inside the fog bank from 5-10 miles from my porch. i have no idea what it was and was wondering if anyone else in my area reported the objecj. slower than any plane, definitely not a star, and not a satelite. i am an avid star gazzer and have seen a ufo at another time. i belive something is out there i just don't know what. i felt at the time that i had just witnessed something very unusual. the last time i saw the object was at about 6:50 when it continued moving toward the right out of my visual range because of trees.
content.summary: Watched an object moving slowly from left to right, with bright pulsating light which changed from red, green and white.

content.detailedDescription: I was with a friend when i was 10 or 11 years old we were riding his honda cub 50 around his yard when we ran out of gas we were geting gas when i looked up an seen this flying disc shaped object very clearly the sky were cloudy and you could make object out clearly,i showed it to dennis whom i was rideing the honda with he dissmissed it as a satillite thi was no satallite it was climbing up not too fast not too slow we or i looked at it for several minutes, then it went into clouds and disappeared i know what i saw! but thats not whats bothering me, this happened in 1968 or 69 i see this image of it awake or a sleep also there is not a day goes by that i do not think about it 2 or three times a day this has been going on for 38 years !!!!! why can't i get this out of my thoughts it just really bothers me and seems the older i get the more i think of that day i know that sounds plum crazy but it is the truth.
content.summary: It happened.

content.detailedDescription:
February 17, 2009 pst

21:40 local time. south of sunriver oregon on south century dr. 

traveling south on south century dr. at n 43 49.321 & w 121 26.600. a bright green-blue light descending from se toward west. viewed for about 2 seconds. transverses an angular change of 35-45 degrees, to the right front of my south bound vehicle, toward the west. clear sky and stars visible, no moon that i noticed. appeared to be below 80 feet (8 story building) agl and descending at about a 5 degree angle toward the west. above some trees on the south side of south century dr.. what i expected to witness was a crash of an airplane because the light looked very much like an aircraft right wing navigation light. i had just passed the fire station on south century dr. and of course that is an area where helicopters land. there is an illuminated helicopter landing pad there. no activity at the fire station that i noticed, no ambulance or other vehicles that i noticed. all quiet at the fire station. as i rounded the turn to the west on south century dr., i stopped the car and rolled down the window. no sounds. no airplane engine sound, no crash, no helicopter rotor blade or engine sounds, nothing. i stopped the car within 20-30 seconds of seeing the light.

no debris trail like a meteor from the light, simply a bright greenish-blue light that came on and went out 2 seconds later.

the light came on and extinguished before the angle it was descending at would have made contact with the ground.

i estimate the light was south of south century dr. after it turns west at the intersection with huntington rd. that would be a distance of about 500-600 feet from my position which was north of the turn about 200-300 feet. i guess speed to be in the 150 mph range. the light moved faster than most helicopters but at about the approach speed of a business jet that could have been inbound to the sunriver airport which is about 3 miles to the north. i consider the fact that both a helicopter landing pad nearby and general aviation airport 3 miles north has nothing to do with the light as i perceive it to not be from an airplane.

i am a retired aviation professional with 25 years and 20,000 hours of flying experience, many aviation related certificates including a licensed aircraft mechanic a&p. i have flow lear jets and cessna citations, boeing 737, 727 and fairchild f-27 airplanes along with 125 different types of general aviation airplanes. it would be difficult to confuse me about airplanes, their lights, sounds and flight characteristics.

i have submitted this report to the northwest ufo group website.
content.summary: Witnessed what i thought was the green right wing tip navigation light of a corporate jet headed for a crash south of the sunriver airport.

content.detailedDescription: My fiance and i were in the living room when i noticed something in the sky to the east where we usually see cars coming down our road from. i guess the thing that got my attention first was the brilliant colors. you could see red, green, white,yellow and sometimes purple with the naked eye. i watched it for a while and it seemed to be moving slowly toward the south. from about 8:00 pm it was in my se direction from my house,when i first noticed it. i went to bed about 11:00 pm that night, and from the time i first noticed it until i went ot bed it had moved from the se to pretty much straight south sky, and then back north almost straight above my house. i think it was the very next night i saw it again and i showed my fiance and i was watching it for a while when she said hey, there's another one. i didn't believe her at first, then she said really, look over here, and sure enough there was another one towards the sw of the house. the next time i saw it i got my telescope since it seemed farther away, and tried to take some pictures but they just looked like apurplish red blob. i did seem to get a pretty good look at it though and it looked round with a flat or slightly domed top and bottom. at one point it looked like a bunch of orange squares rotating around it from my left to right with a brilliant white on the top and the bottom, this continued for a while and all of a sudden it looked like purple exploded out the top and bottom of it simultaniously. shortly after i first saw it i got on the internet to see if a satelite would look like this and the only info i found was that it would look bright white. i have seen this thing in the sky quite frequently when there is no clouds, even just the other night. i finally found someone to ask about it and am doing so to clearify this as to what it could be. i guess what added to my interest is what else has happened to me personally in about the same time period i have been seeing this object. on 3-9-09 i fell and probably tore my rotor cuff. this has nothing to do with this, accept i knew i would probably be going to the doctor about it as it was really sore. yesterday, wednesday 3-11-09 i woke up for about the fourth time since about last summer with what i had been calling scratches on the upper back part of my right leg. only this time i also had them on the front part of my leg just below my beltline going downward about 5 inches long. prior to this i thought i had just did this myself, accept this time i could see them much better. there was about 4 marks spaced about 3 and a half inches wide and about 6 inches up and down. the weird thing was one line going down y'ed off into 2 line and one of those two y'ed into another line all totally continus like it formed out of one line with no gaps between. on the back of my leg was even more distinct or deaper marks only running horizontal just under my but cheak. this is where they had been before. looking closer with a mirror, one of the lines in back of my leg y'ed off twice like the one in front. i guess the y ing off with no gap in the line got my attention the most. well i went to my doctor today and had him look at my shoulder and then i said i would like him to look at my scratches. i told him it happens in my sleep, and i don't even wake up, i just notice a slight burning sensation when i content.detailedDescription:
To quickly preface this

     im currently writing a book about an important scientific discovery located within the rocky mountains of the united states, known as the wis (western interior seaway) impact project. this unique discovery has allowed me to be the first person to locate and study the first major physical evidence of the dinosaur extinction, which occurred 65.2 million years ago. this physical evidence exists within an ancient 300 ft tall by 75 mile wide asteroid impact debris pile. the physical evidence located within this debris pile includes: fossil dinosaur bones (millions), showing evidence of high speed ballistic impacts, along with strange "signature" impact materials from the impacting asteroid, such as large iron (fe) spherules (millions), some of which, are so strange, that do not
currently register as any known substance thus far within several series of professional testing.

a strange thing happened on june 6th 2002

     this occurred at the wis discovery site, during the fifth and most important day after the initial discovery of the impact debris pile itself.  i would estimate that it was about 9:20 pm. it had just gotten dark on the ledge of a mountain where i was camped. the camp was located about 1 mile away from the original discovery site. i was inside the tent when my father (and recently deceased co-partner) called out to me about a bright light moving across the sky. i figured he was either seeing the space station or a satellite in orbit. i walked out from the tent, and also saw a bright whitish light streaking across the sky at a high rate of speed. i instantly knew that no plane could cover that distance so quickly. the light reached us in about 1-2 seconds after i walked out of the door. the light then literally stops and hangs in mid air over the initial wis discovery site location. it hangs perfectly still for about 1 1/2 minutes. then...It changes course direction and shoots off at an incredibly high rate of speed again. both me and my father sat discussing the incident for about 5-6 minutes until we noticed that two air force jets (flying in formation) came chasing after the object in question. the two military jets changed course direction in the exact same spot as the lighted object in question had also performed minutes earlier. that concludes the facts as i know them. it is now pure speculation as to what that object was, and why it was there that specific night.

     the possibility exists that a mini neutron flux occurred during this large asteroid impact upon north america millions of years ago. a neutron flux is the process in which heavy elements are created during the supernova of a star. should this indeed be the case, the wis impact project will introduce a series of new stable elements that mainstream science has not yet seen before, such as unfamiliar isotopes of iron (fe) and possible theoretical elements like element 115 and beyond. most of the materials within my research samples do not seem to have the actual weight required to be considered one of the super heavy element groups. it will likely turn out to be an unusual isotope of iron (fe) and other surrounding elements on the periodic table. these samples need immediate access to the most advanced testing equipment around the world.

     i have sincerely dedicated most of my time to the wis project and still research steadily to figure out that strange connection ever since. this project involves a dedicated knowledge within 8-10 separate areas of academic science. no single person has achieved a degree within that many fields. they simply dont exist. by the beginning of 2003, i have only existed within a scientific monastery in near complete isolation ever since, pondering and working to further understand the true aspects and importance of this incredible discovery.

     i thought that you might find this project and that strange occurrence interesting, and possibly worthy of further research on your part. please feel free to actually review the evidence and view the information and evidence photos located on my web page.

{pid}

simply click the photos button, and browse through the wis project
photos album.

i would really appreciate it any opinions

for the world is hollowand now i have touched the sky,

quentin {pid2}

wis project scientist
field & research

content.detailedDescription: Early morning 6:45 am. june 1st, 1990. newhall / santa clarita, ca.  beautiful clear skies, unlimited visibility.  driving on circle j road (now is oak ridge road) towards san fernando road. there is a large, 200 feet across, dry wash basin paralleling san fernando road, and on the other side of the wash basin is a line of high power electrical lines. san fernando road was under construction, reduced to less driving lanes due to widening of the road. i come to stop at the intersection facing san fernando rd. it is a "t" intersection which at this time has a temporary traffic signal directly in front of me on the other side of the road, approx distance 60 feet.   as i am waiting for the red light to change i noticed something dark hovering in the sky to the left and at the same visual height as the traffic light but stationary and adjacent to the high power line directly across the wash. how could you miss it?  it is flat black or very dark gray in color, stealth looking, a large object approx. 100 feet across. i do not remember any sound associated with it.  the shape is hard to describe and i have never seen anything like it in pictures. it basically was a disk shape with a cap top that extends slightly over the sides, small vertical straight sides or slightly angled in top to bottom,  and a flat bottom thats diameter was less than the cap. it had details, shapes on the sides below the cap. the visual of the object was obscured slightly by what i would associate observing heat coming off a highway in the summer. its position is approx. 400 yds direct line of sight from me at 10 o'clock, vertical . the object was stationary in the air, i do not remember it moving in any way, just the heat waves obscuring the view. i did not drive away when the light changed and chose to stay and continue observing the craft for a couple light changes. cars were stopped behind me honking their horn for me to proceed so i finally did pointing to what i was observing, driving up the road half mile to the fire station on san fernando. where i parked, got out and i could still see the object. i continued observing for a few minutes realizing i was late for work. i had to go. it was a weird experience,  i felt maybe i was the only one that could see it. did anybody else see it?
content.summary: Observed daylight visual of craft hovering adjacent to high power electrical tower while sitting at traffic light.

content.detailedDescription:
It was a warm clear summer night. i was sitting on my boat doing some late night-early morning fishing as i had often done, when i noticed a bright light approximately 10 miles or so away.I was facing that direction already so it was no effort to look up. this was a very common sight because the international airport is about 25 miles to the south east. at first i thought it was an aircraft with it's landing lights on, but after a minute or so i realized the aircraft was going away from me.
i thought it was odd because i could not remember ever seeing landing lights on a plane that was going away from me. i contemplated what it was.
i thought it might be a jet with it's afterburner on. the aircraft was climbing steadily at about a 30 degree angle or so. i figured it might be the sun shining on it from the horizon. i watched as the light moved further and further away. it was also getting smaller and eventually kind of looked like a star. then all of a sudden it took an immediate 90 degree sharp turn to the left (west) and increased its speed to an incredible rate and disappeared. i have never seen anything that could turn on a dime like that and i have never seen an aircraft go that fast before and i was in the military. after i got home i told my wife what i saw. i also told my co-workers what i saw when i went back to work.
i am a fairly intelligent person, and i never believed in ufos before that.
ever since then i am completely convinced that the "aircraft" was in fact either a ufo or some kind of military aircraft that the world does not know about yet.
content.summary: I saw a bright light moving away from me it took an incredibly sharp 90 deg turn to the left  (west) and sped off  at speeds i have never seen.

content.detailedDescription:
On feb 11th 2009 at roughly 6pm while driving home my wife and i saw a black triangle craft with 3 lights underneath it heading in a ne direction in the early evening sky underneath the cloudcover. an airliner that was passing thru the same area nearly hit it but veered away and up. we pulled over to check it out and i grabbed my camera from the back seat (i always keep it with me in the car). after the near miss the triangle made a tight circle and headed back sw. shortly thereafter it appeared another airliner was coming thru the same area as the triangle craft was making its turn but it was much to large and actually appeared to be a diamond shaped craft with many lighs around it including a forward and rear facing directed type spotlight. this diamond craft was 4 or 5 times the size of the triangle craft but unlike the smaller triangle it was still mostly in the bottom cloud cover so details were obscured. the diamond made a wider and slower turn and matched up with the smaller triangle craft heading sw. i snapped the picture as the triangle was beggining its turn, i only wish i would of snapped a shot of the diamond craft but my wife and i were far to blown away trying to figure out what it was. very interesting sighting and for what its worth it was my first.

some additional notes...

the triangle craft was solid black with 3 lights underneath it near each tip, very easily viewed with the naked eye. this craft moved slowly and smoothly, and when it turned it made an impossibly tight turn. we heard no sound from this one although we heard the plane it nearly collided with perfectly well as it passed overhead.

the diamond craft was truely massive, hence the primary reason i didnt snap a picture of it i think, my wife and i were stunned (im still kicking myself over this). i dont recall a noise from this craft but my wife distinctly recalls a low humming or electrical buzzing sound coming from it. we've discussed this sighting many times since it happened and we've come to the conclusion that the diamond craft wasnt actually in the bottom of the cloud layer but was instead most likely projecting the clouds above it on its surface as a form of camoflauge perhaps. this craft moved very slowly and smoothly.

we live relatively near a small airport that is used by small cesna type planes and we see planes around constantly. i think this strengthens this sighting as opposed to weakening it however because we are painfully familiar with what planes look and act like in the skies. these 2 craft were not like any civilian or military planes we've ever seen, and that includes the stealth fighter/bomber.

if theres any way we can help with additional info please let us know.
content.summary: Triangle craft has near miss with plane then is joined by massive diamond craft.

content.detailedDescription: I went to take the dogs out and noticed a very bright star to the west of my position.  i looked directly above me and noticed it was a cloudy night and thought it was odd that i could see this star.  i walked out the the road to get a better view and noticed the object was below the clouds.  i watched it for about 5 min and seen it move first vertical and then horizontal to the north.  i went inside and asked my wife to come out and take a look at the light.  she did not know what to say.  she just kept asking me "what is it"  we watched it for about 5 more min and it made some more vertical and horizontal moves but never moved beyond my view.  i went in to the house to get my night vision binoculars (took about 2 min) and when i returned the object was gone.  i scanned the sky with the night vision but never could find the object.  i have went out on and off to see if it has returned for the past 30 min but nothing has come back.  the clouds have lifted and stars have become more visible but nothing in the area of the object.  i have heard of several reports as of late from areas around where i live but never seen anything myself. it just bothers me that i can't come up with a reasonable excuse for what i have just witnessed.
content.summary: Star like light but much brighter.  it was about at a 35 degree angle from where i was watching it.
